description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a passionate qualified Social Worker looking for a new challenge working within a creative, confident and ambitious organisation?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We want to create a workforce that is brave, agile and innovative that listens, learns and celebrates success and we currently have a range of Social Worker opportunities across our Adult Social Care Teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;strong&gt;About the roles&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will be working in one of our generic teams alongside Occupational Therapists within a locality, hospital setting or Safeguarding Team alongside other professional colleagues working with adults, their family and carers to understand what really matters to them through a strengths based approach. We believe that by working closely with our communities, the NHS and our partners, understanding local needs, working with individuals in a positive and responsive way, we can make a real difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a social work qualification and be registered with Social Work England&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy working in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the passion to promote people’s strengths and the ability to make a difference&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you should have the ability to travel to and access a variety of premises across Oxfordshire and meet the requirements set out in selection criteria within the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;



&lt;strong&gt;In return, you will receive:&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular formal and informal support and supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive CPD opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An ASYE programme for Newly Qualified Social Workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working options (we promote and support agile working)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High quality digital equipment provided to all staff. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safe, supportive and positive working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave up to 29 days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to the Local Government Pension Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust supervision and training opportunities in these roles enabling you to develop your skills, plus a career progression scheme, to help you progress professionally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In line with County Council policy, we also offer a relocation package up to a maximum of £8,000 to cover reimbursement of expenses for newly appointed employees who need to move home to take a job with Oxfordshire County Council (conditions apply)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



 
&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to know more?&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Further details about the responsibilities and requirements of the role are contained in the Job Description and Person Specification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
